
Last evening we discussed with Robin Gibbs an e-mail we would send to the 
"List of 100," telling them to be circumspect with electronic mail 
communications.  I prepared a short e-mail and had Barrett Reasoner take a 
look and approve it
last night.  Here it is:
_________________________________


You have been identified as a person possibly having contact with the power 
situation in California.  This e-mail is to remind you that the dissemination 
of information should be given careful consideration.  You should be prudent 
in the circulation of electronic mail relating to your work and activities.

__________________________________